"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421644","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-10-22","<p>The Government has a manifesto commitment to extend the Right to Buy to 1.3 million housing association tenants.</p><p>The deal we have made with the National Housing Federation ensures that housing associations will give their tenants the opportunity to buy their home with an equivalent discount to the Right to Buy, delivering the manifesto commitment.</p><p>The Government is in discussion with the National Housing Federation and the housing association sector to ensure that the right arrangements are put in place to support the implementation and delivery of the proposals.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2015-10-22T15:19:33.863Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421644/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421644/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421644/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-10-15","Right to Buy Scheme","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what information he received about risks connected with the proposed right to buy scheme during the planning of that scheme.","false","Biography information for Mr Roger Godsiff","Birmingham, Hall Green","Mr Roger Godsiff","12047"
