"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421716","Department for Transport","false","2015-10-22","<p>The Department for Business, Innovation and Skills (BIS) is responsible for funding the Trailblazer apprenticeships programme and the industry is developing a standard for an HGV Driver apprenticeship. Funding for obtaining an HGV licence is not currently in scope of Trailblazers but this is under review. BIS will consider what the new funding model will be with the introduction of the new apprenticeship levy.</p><br />","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2015-10-22T14:39:06.543Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421716/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421716/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421716/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-10-15","Large Goods Vehicles: Licensing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, whether his Department plans to provide assistance to companies in training personnel to gain HGV qualifications.","false","Biography information for David Simpson","Upper Bann","David Simpson","12030"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421717","Department for Transport","false","2015-10-22","<p>The Department recognises that there is a high demand for HGV drivers in the UK and that there is a shortage, manifesting itself in pressure on costs, delays to some deliveries and the recruitment of people from outside the UK.</p><br /> <br />","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2015-10-22T14:59:51.813Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421717/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421717/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421717/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-10-15","Large Goods Vehicle Drivers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what assessment he has made of the adequacy of the number of HGV drivers in the UK relative to demand.","false","Biography information for David Simpson","Upper Bann","David Simpson","12031"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421718","Department for Transport","false","2015-10-22","<p>The Department is working with its motoring services agencies to reduce times and delays in obtaining a driving test appointment and medical licence renewals.</p><br /><p>Other government activity is helping jobseekers join the industry, retraining ex-military personnel and supporting apprenticeships.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2015-10-22T15:04:45.787Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421718/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421718/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421718/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-10-15","Large Goods Vehicle Drivers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what plans his Department has to increase the number of HGV drivers.","false","Biography information for David Simpson","Upper Bann","David Simpson","12032"
