/td><td><p><br></p></td><td><p><br></p></td><td><p><br></p></td><td><p><br></p></td><td><p><br></p></td><td><p><br></p></td></tr><tr><td colspan="10"><p>These figures are used for the purposes of statistical reporting; more reliable case information for the purposes of managing the prison estate is not centrally held. The figures in these tables have been drawn from administrative IT systems which, as with any large scale recording system, are subject to possible errors with data entry and processing. <br></p></td><td><p><br></p></td><td><p><br></p></td><td><p><br></p></td><td><p><br></p></td><td><p><br></p></td></tr></tbody></table><br />","South West Bedfordshire","Andrew Selous",,"2015-10-29T13:55:26.817Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421750/answer","Biography information for Andrew Selous","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421750/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421750/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-10-15","Prison Sentences","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, for which offences prisoners serving imprisonment for public protection sentences were convicted on the most recent date for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Andy Slaughter","Hammersmith","Andy Slaughter","12127"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421751","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-10-21","<p>As I stated in my Written Ministerial Statement of 15 October, the department has withdrawn the procurement for an external provider for compliance and enforcement services. Therefore permanent members of staff employed by Her Majesty’s Courts and Tribunals Service in compliance and enforcement roles will remain as civil servants.</p>","North West Cambridgeshire","Mr Shailesh Vara",,"2015-10-21T09:54:18.63Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421751/answer","Biography information for Mr Shailesh Vara","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421751/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421751/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-10-15","HM Courts and Tribunals Service: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, pursuant to the Written Statement by the Minister for the Courts and Legal Aid of 15 October 2015, HCWS 237, on HM Courts & Tribunal Service, if it is his policy for staff of that service to remain civil servants.","false","Biography information for Andy Slaughter","Hammersmith","Andy Slaughter","12126"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421752","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-10-20","<p>There are currently no plans to initiate an internal review.</p>","North West Cambridgeshire","Mr Shailesh Vara",,"2015-10-20T16:31:14.147Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421752/answer","Biography information for Mr Shailesh Vara","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421752/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421752/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-10-15","HM Courts and Tribunals Service: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, pursuant to the Written Statement by the Minister for Courts and Legal Aid, of 15 October 2015, HCWS 239, on HM Courts and Tribunals Service, if he will initialise an internal review into the decision to discontinue the procurement competition referred to in the statement, with a view to subsequent publication of that review.","false","Biography information for Andy Slaughter","Hammersmith","Andy Slaughter","12149"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421753","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-11-06","<p>As I told the House on 15 October, we took the decision not to outsource HMCTS compliance and enforcement services to a single supplier because of the need to ensure that any contract we let provided the best value for the taxpayer.</p><p><br> The total cost of the Compliance and Enforcement Service Project as of end of September 2015 was £8,723,645.</p>","North West Cambridgeshire","Mr Shailesh Vara",,"2015-11-06T14:52:32.267Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421753/answer","Biography information for Mr Shailesh Vara","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421753/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421753/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-10-15","HM Courts and Tribunals Service: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, pursuant to the Statement by the Minister for Courts and Legal Aid, of 15 October 2015, HCWS 239, on HM Courts and Tribunals Service, what the total cost to the Exchequer was of the discontinued procurement process referred to in the statement.","false","Biography information for Andy Slaughter","Hammersmith","Andy Slaughter","12150"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421754","Department for Transport","false","2015-10-20","<p>Ticket gates barriers are operated and provided by a number of different operating companies at national rail stations, Docklands Light Railway, TfL Overground and tube stations across London. No such estimate has been made across all stations in London.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2015-10-20T09:39:28.097Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421754/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421754/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421754/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-10-15","Railway Stations: Greater London","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what estimate his Department has made of the cost to the public purse of ticket barriers at stations in London being left open.","false","Biography information for Andy Slaughter","Hammersmith","Andy Slaughter","12079"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421755","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-10-20","<p>A consultation on the proposed postgraduate Master’s loan scheme was held earlier in the year. The consultation covered proposed terms and conditions, including an age eligibility criterion and the eligibility of distance learning. Consultation responses are currently being analysed and the Department will respond in the autumn.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson","12019 ; 12022","2015-10-20T14:50:28.79Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421755/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421755/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421755/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-10-15","Postgraduate Education","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what the reasons are for his proposal to exclude taught masters students who are over the age of 30 from the new postgraduate loans scheme proposed for England.","false","Biography information for Paul Blomfield","Sheffield Central","Paul Blomfield","12018"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421756","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-10-20","<p>A consultation on the proposed postgraduate Master’s loan scheme was held earlier in the year. The consultation covered proposed terms and conditions, including an age eligibility criterion and the eligibility of distance learning. Consultation responses are currently being analysed and the Department will respond in the autumn.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson","12018 ; 12022","2015-10-20T14:50:29.437Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421756/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421756/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421756/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-10-15","Postgraduate Education","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what the reasons are for the proposed exclusion from the new postgraduate loans scheme proposed for England of taught masters students who are studying via distance learning at a minimum of 50 per cent intensity.","false","Biography information for Paul Blomfield","Sheffield Central","Paul Blomfield","12019"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421757","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-10-20","<p>A consultation on the proposed postgraduate Master’s loan scheme was held earlier in the year. The consultation covered proposed terms and conditions, including an age eligibility criterion and the eligibility of distance learning. Consultation responses are currently being analysed and the Department will respond in the autumn.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson","12018 ; 12019","2015-10-20T14:50:29.987Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421757/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421757/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421757/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-10-15","Postgraduate Education","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what the reasons are for the proposal to include in the new postgraduate loans scheme proposed for England part-time taught masters students studying at a minimum of 50 per cent intensity not via distance learning.","false","Biography information for Paul Blomfield","Sheffield Central","Paul Blomfield","12022"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421758","Department of Health","false","2015-10-23","<p>In 2014 Health and Wellbeing Needs Assessments were carried out at all Immigration Removal Centres to ascertain the needs of the detainees, which in turn informed the quality and standard of services commissioned by NHS England, from 1 September 2014, to meet those needs.</p><br /><p>National standards have been developed, against which health care providers are measured as part of contract management. A suite of indicators of performance are now in place to support this and to provide national data to demonstrate improvements in service delivery and outcomes.</p><p><strong></strong></p>","Ipswich","Ben Gummer",,"2015-10-23T13:15:46.82Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421758/answer","Biography information for Ben Gummer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421758/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421758/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-10-15","Health Services: Detention Centres","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what assessment he made of the effect of NHS England taking over responsibility for commissioning health services within the immigration detention estate in England on the adequacy of health provision within that estate.","false","Biography information for Paul Blomfield","Sheffield Central","Paul Blomfield","12015"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421759","Department of Health","false","2015-10-23","<p>The National Institute for Health and Care Excellence (NICE) is currently appraising nivolumab for <em>Melanoma (advanced, unresectable, metastatic)</em> <em>- [ID845]</em>, and the anticipated publication date for its final guidance is May 2016. Further information is available on NICE’s website at:</p><br /><p><a href="http://www.nice.org.uk/guidance/indevelopment/gid-tag515" target="_blank">www.nice.org.uk/guidance/indevelopment/gid-tag515</a></p><p><strong></strong></p><p>In the absence of NICE guidance, funding decisions for individual treatments should be made by the relevant National Health Service commissioner, based on an assessment of the available evidence. Commissioners are also required to have processes in place for the consideration of exceptional funding requests. <br></p><p>NHS England is responsible for commissioning chemotherapy in England and has advised that it will not usually develop a commissioning policy on treatments which are undergoing NICE appraisal. Nivolumab is undergoing assessment and is not yet routinely funded for patients.</p><p><strong></strong></p><p><strong></strong></p>","Mid Norfolk","George Freeman",,"2015-10-23T13:08:26.11Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421759/answer","Biography information for George Freeman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421759/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421759/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-10-15","Nivolumab","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, if he will take steps to ensure NHS melanoma patients are able to access nivolumab before its appraisal by NICE.","false","Biography information for Paula Sherriff","Dewsbury","Paula Sherriff","12038"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421760","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-10-23","<p>Successive Governments have upheld the principle of legal professional privilege, which means they do not disclose whether legal advice has been sought, or the content of any such advice that may have been obtained. I would also refer you to the Attorney General, my right hon. Friend the Member for Kenilworth and Southam’s (Jeremy Wright) answer of 12 October (PQ 10450).</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2015-10-23T13:53:55.803Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421760/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421760/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421760/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-10-15","Counter-terrorism","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, pursuant to the Prime Minister's oral statement of 7 September 2015, Official Report, column 30, on counter-terrorism, whether the Foreign and Commonwealth Office's legal adviser was consulted on the legal basis for the military action against Reyaad Khan in Syria.","false","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","12130"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421761","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-10-28","<p>UKTI Defence and Security Organisation expects to publish the next list of priority markets before the end of the financial year. Until then, the current list remains extant.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2015-10-28T14:49:17.22Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421761/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421761/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421761/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-10-15","UK Trade and Investment Defence and Security Organisation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, pursuant to the Answer to Question 3393 of 30 June 2015, when the UKTI Defence and Security Organisation priority markets list for 2015-16 will be published.","false","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","12128"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421762","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-10-23","<p>The Prime Minister, my right hon. Friend the Member for Witney (Mr Cameron) has invited President Sisi to the UK and the visit will take before the end of this year. Discussions will take place with President Sisi on a wide range of issues of mutual interest, including trade and security.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2015-10-23T13:52:58.743Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421762/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421762/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421762/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-10-15","State Visits: Egypt","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, pursuant to the Answer of 29 June 2015 to Question 4073, on what date the planned visit of President Sisi of Egypt to the UK will take place; and whether he plans to discuss the supply of military, security and police equipment with President Sisi during his visit.","false","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","12129"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421763","Prime Minister","false","2015-10-21","<p>As I said in my oral statement of 7 September 2015, <em>Official Report</em>, column 23, the action we took was entirely lawful.</p>","Witney","Mr David Cameron",,"2015-10-21T14:11:01.707Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421763/answer","Biography information for Mr David Cameron","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421763/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421763/answer",,,,,"23","Prime Minister","Prime Minister","2015-10-15","Counter-terrorism","1","House of Commons","To ask the Prime Minister, pursuant to the Answer to Question 9571 of 14 September 2015, whether the Attorney General was clear there was a legal basis for this action in domestic law.","false","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","12154"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421764","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2015-10-22","<p>£28,780 worth of fresh milk has been purchased by Eurest (Defra’s catering services provider) since 1 April 2015. This is distributed across Defra sites on a supply and demand basis. All milk purchased by Eurest is sourced from the UK. Eurest pay above the average monthly farm gate price for all our milk, which includes use at Nobel House.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2015-10-22T10:32:48.587Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421764/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421764/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/421764/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2015-10-15","Department for Environment, Food, and Rural Affairs: Milk","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, how much (a) fair price and (b) non-fair price milk was purchased for Nobel House, 17 Smith Square, London in August 2015; and what plans she has to ensure that only fair price milk is used at Nobel House, 17 Smith Square, London.","false","Biography information for Sir Mark Hendrick","Preston","Mr Mark Hendrick","12133"
